<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="804" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-31"><hi rend="italic">October 31,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>New cabinet contains following changes: Minister of the interior, Alexis
                            Obolensky; minister of finance, Romaroff; minister of justice, Koni;
                            minister of education, Krosovsky; minister of ways and communications,
                            Ziegler Von Sgaffhausen.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>